
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
### CÓDIGO ###

	ls -pmu
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
### LS ###

man ls 
	−p        Write a <slash> ('/') after each filename if that file is a directory.
	−m        Stream output format; list pathnames across the page, separated by a <comma> character followed by a <space> character. 
			  Use a <newline> character as  the  list terminator and after the separator sequence when there is not room on a line for the next list entry. 
			  This option disables long format output.
	−u        Use time of last access (see the Base Definitions volume of POSIX.1‐2008, <sys_stat.h>) 
			  instead of last modification of the file for sorting  (−t)  or  writing (−l).

